6. Execution Normalization Layer (Core Moat Layer)
All events converted into:
ExecutionEvent {
 id
 org_id
 source
 type
 actors
 timestamp
 raw_content
 structured_metadata
 sensitivity_score
 }
Then embedded using pgvector.
This becomes the Execution Knowledge Graph.

7. Sensitivity & Filtering System (Dashboard Controls)
Users configure:
7.1 Data Controls
Toggle:
• Allow numeric metrics in output
 • Mask percentages
 • Mask revenue numbers
 • Mask client names
 • Mask company names
 • Mask personal names
 • Mask internal strategy references
Each has:
 ON / OFF / Ask before publish

7.2 Content Tone Controls
Default output style:
• Educational
 • Insightful
 • Tactical
 • Contrarian
 • Reflective
 • Executive summary
Tone profile stored per org.

7.3 Redaction Strictness
Low → Moderate → High
Redaction engine runs before draft generation.

8. Insight Detection Engine
Automatic ingestion runs:
Event classifier


Insight detection scoring


Correlation detection (cross-source pattern)


Confidence threshold check


If confidence > threshold:
Slack Bot posts:
“New insight detected from Zoom call + Slack discussion.
 Generate draft?”
User can:
• Generate draft
 • Ignore
 • Mark as internal only
 • Save to knowledge base

9. Draft Generation
Three variations generated:
Educational


Tactical breakdown


Narrative reflection


All passed through:
• Sensitivity filter
 • Tone control
 • Org voice model (future)

10. Slack Primary Flow
Example Flow
Zoom call ends →
 Transcript ingested →
 Insight detected →
 Slack bot posts in #growth:
“Insight detected: Activation improved after onboarding simplification.
 Generate draft?”
User clicks →
 Slack modal opens →
 Editable draft →
 Publish →
LinkedIn API called →
 Success confirmation.

